text:
Ralamboarison Named WAC Player Of The Week
Tsara Ralamboarison has been named the Western Athletic Conference Player of the Week, following her standout performance at the Red Rocks Invitational, where she finished second. She recorded an impressive score of -2 under par (70) in a challenging single-day format. Ralamboarison's score was just one stroke shy of winning the individual title, as weather conditions limited the tournament to nine holes over two days.
By the Numbers- Ralamboarison finished the week with a -2 under par (70) score.
- She was one of only 14 golfers to shoot under par during the tournament.
- Ralamboarison's performance marks her first WAC Player of the Week honor.

The Redhawks golf team is preparing for the upcoming Dr. Donnis Thompson Invitational in Hawai'i, where Ralamboarison will look to build on her recent success.
